The paper deals with multi-agent systems, communication constraints, and decision-making under uncertainty, which are all topics that fall under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) and their application to multi-agent systems, which is a subfield of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for decision-making under constraints, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses probabilistic modeling and Monte Carlo methods, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
